'''J. Patrick Doyle''' (born 4 June 1963 in [[Midland, Michigan|Midland]], [[Michigan]]) is the [[CEO]] of [[Domino's Pizza]] and has been since March 2010. He has been an executive with the company since 1997. From 1991 to 1997, he was an executive with the [[Gerber Products Company]]. Prior to that, he was an executive with [[Intervascular]] and the erstwhile [[First Chicago Bank]]. He also serves as a director for [[Best Buy]]. He was previously a director of [[G&K Services]] and [[Alsea]]. He holds an [[MBA]] from the [[University of Chicago]], and an [[economics]] degree from the [[University of Michigan]].<ref name=Bloomberg>{{cite web|title=Bloomberg profile|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/people/person.asp?personId=8117520&privcapId=3132512|publisher=Bloomberg News|accessdate=7 January 2016}}</ref><ref name=WSJ>{{cite web|title=J. Patrick Doyle: The Weekend Interview|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-weekend-interview-with-j-patrick-doyle-how-pizza-became-a-growth-stock-1426286353|website=[[Wall Street Journal]]|accessdate=7 January 2016}}</ref><ref name=PWC>{{cite web|title=Video Interview|url=http://www.pwc.com/us/en/ceo-survey/ceo-interviews/patrick-doyle-dominos-pizza.html|publisher=[[PriceWaterhouseCoopers]]|accessdate=7 January 2016}}</ref> He is also a member of the Sigma Phi Society.

