posed [[co-operative banking]] groups of whole Italy.<ref name=2017bankinggroup>{{cite press release|url=https://www.cassacentrale.it/ccbcontent0.jsp?XD=5671&LANGUAGE=IT|title=CASSA CENTRALE BANCA PRESENTA LA CANDIDATURA A CAPOGRUPPO|date=30 January 2017|access-date=17 July 2017|publisher=Cassa Centrale Banca|language=Italian}}</ref> The other candidate was [[ICCREA Banca]] (and [[Raiffeisen Landesbank Südtirol – Cassa Centrale Raiffeisen dell'Alto Adige]] for South Tyrol autonomous province only). A new Italian law required all co-operative banks of Italy to join a banking group, which the central institution has power to recapitalize individual member banks, but the central institution itself would be owned by the member banks in a majority. Cassa Centrale Banca - Credito Cooperativo del Nord Est had proposed to change their name to Cassa Centrale Banca – Credito Cooperativo Italiano.<ref name=2017bankinggroup/>
==Joint ventures== Cassa Centrale Banca had a joint venture "Casse Rurali – Raiffeisen Finanziaria" with its [[Raiffeisen Landesbank Südtirol – Cassa Centrale Raiffeisen dell'Alto Adige|South Tyrol counterpart]]. The joint venture was the largest shareholder of [[Investitionsbank Trentino Südtirol – Mediocredito Trentino Alto Adige|Investitionsbank – Mediocredito]] of South Tyrol - Trentino autonomous region.
Cassa Centrale Banca had another joint venture Nord Est Asset Management S.A. (NEAM in short).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cassacentrale.it/wwwhome1.jsp?XD=3302&LANGUAGE=IT|title= NORD EST FUND |access-date=17 July 2017|publisher=Cassa Centrale Banca|language=Italian}}</ref> ==Shareholders== The bank was owned by the member banks directly. However, in order to sell 25% shares to [[DZ Bank]], a new holding company '''Centrale Finanziaria del Nord Est''' was established in 2007, in order to make the member banks had a controlling influence to the central institute. ==See also== * [[Cassa del Trentino]], development bank of Trentino
